<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>app.oryxis.Oryxis</id>

  <name>Oryxis</name>
  <summary>Rust-native SSH client</summary>

  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>AGPL-3.0-or-later</project_license>

  <developer id="app.oryxis">
    <name>Wilson Glasser</name>
  </developer>

  <description>
    <p>
      Oryxis is a modern, Rust-native SSH client with a focus on privacy and
      speed. It keeps your connections in a local encrypted vault, syncs them
      directly between your devices over a peer-to-peer link, and embeds a full
      terminal.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Encrypted local vault (Argon2id + ChaCha20Poly1305) for hosts, keys and identities</li>
      <li>Peer-to-peer device sync over QUIC, with no mandatory cloud</li>
      <li>Embedded terminal with split panes and session groups</li>
      <li>Jump hosts, SOCKS/HTTP/command proxies and SFTP</li>
      <li>Standalone port forwarding (local, remote and dynamic)</li>
      <li>Per-session AI chat with command execution</li>
      <li>Kubernetes and cloud integrations</li>
      <li>17 interface languages, with right-to-left support</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

